Key Match Events: Ajdin Hrustic scored the opening goal for Australia in the 29th minute.
Lachlan Yengi extended Australia's lead with a goal in the 62nd minute.
Rakib Hossain scored a consolation goal for Bangladesh in the 83rd minute.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia, with a five-point lead at the top of Group I, played their fifth World Cup qualifying fixture against winless Bangladesh.
Australia had already secured a top-two finish in Group I and a place in the next round of Asian World Cup qualifying.
Australia had a strong qualifying campaign with four wins from four matches, including a 7-0 thrashing of Bangladesh in their first encounter.
Bangladesh, placed 184th in FIFA's world rankings, were essentially playing for pride.
